dct_title_s: Map to accompany notes of a journey from Bida in Nupe, to Kano in Haussa; performed by Dr. W. B. Baikie, R.N. 1862
dct_description_sm: Dr. Baikie's route shown in red. Relief shown by hachures. Approximate territories of indigenous groups are shown. "This Map has been reconstructed from Dr. Baikie's Original Journal in the Foreign Office and founded upon some additional Latitudes and Longitudes --- J.A." From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 37 (1867), pp. 92-108; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.37 1867
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1867.
